collectionMetadata.name: State Courts Clearance Rate Figures
collectionMetadata.description: Dataset contains the annual clearance rates figures of the State Courts

datasetMetadata.name: State Courts Clearance Rate Figures, 2016 to 2022
datasetMetadata.description: Clearance rate is the number of cases disposed expressed as a percentage of the number of cases filed in the same year. The clearance rate can exceed 100% as those disposed of are not necessarily a subset of the filings in that year.
